cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a ProM plug-in for interactive artifact-centric process discovery tool. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of event data to automatically discover composite state machines representing artifact-centric processes. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of event data to discover process models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the quantification of interactions among different artifacts, which could involve the use of machine learning techniques. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the visualization of interactions among different artifacts, which could involve the design of user interfaces.
